value: Provenance: J.R. Holliday, 1927. Georgius Klotz, M.D. Francofurti ad Moenum (bklabel). Bookplate "from the library of the Earl of Ashburnham" dated May 1897. Price codes on e.p.

Notitia dignitatum.
Notitia vtraqve cvm orientis tvm occidentis vltra Arcadii Honoriiqve Caesarvm tempora, illustre uetustatis monumentum, imò thesaurus prorsum incomparabilis
With: Luciano Samosatensis ... Basileae: Io. Froben, 1521.
Colophon dated: mense Octobri 1521.
Title within decorative, historiated woodcut border.
Printer's device in woodcut on verso of last leaf.
Edited by Sigmund Gelen
Printers' names from colophon.
Printer's mark with inscription "Froben" on title page and verso of last leaf.
With numerous woodcut illustrations throughout. Woodcuts hand-coloured.
Binding: sprinkled calf, border (double g. fillet); spine & board edges g.t., g. lettering on spine labels; marbled e.p.
Provenance: purchased 1891. T.p. inscr. dated 1582. Library label, crest of John Montagu, duke of Montagu. H.E. Jones ... Gloucester ... artist's materials (label).
Binding: quarter blind-stamped pigskin, wooden sides; raised bands, spine unlettered; remains of clasps.

Apologiae Erasmi Roterodami omnes, aduersus eos, qui illum locis aliquot, in suis libris, non satis circunspecte sunt calumniati. :

Notitia utraque cum orientis tum occidentis ultra Arcadii Honoriique Caesarum tempora, illustre uetustatis monumentum, imò thesaurus prorsum incomparabilis. : Praecedit aute[m] D. Andreæ Alciati libellus, De magistratib. ciuilibusq́[ue] ac militaribus officijs, partim ex hac ipsa Notitia, partim aliunde desumptus. Cui succedit descriptio urbis Romæ, quae sub titulo Pub. Victoris circumfertur: & altera urbis Constantinopolitanae incerto autore, nunqua[m] antehac typis excusa, imperialium uidelicet ac primariaru[m] sedium utriusq[ue] Reipub. Sub iungitur Notitijs uetustus liber De rebus bellicis ad Theodosium Aug. & filios eius Arcadium atq[ue] Honorium, ut uidetur, scriptus, incerto autore. Item, ne quid de antiquo exemplari ommitteretur, Disputatio Adriani Aug. & Epicteti philosophi..
